pullRequest.title: Create Log Wrapper and Replace Base library logging
pullRequest.bodyText:
Fixes #1377
This PR is [ready] for review.
Risk
This PR makes [minor] API changes.
Testing Plan

 I have verified that I have not introduced new warnings in this PR (or explain why below)
 I have run the unit tests with this PR
 I have tested this PR against Core and verified behavior (if applicable, if not applicable, explain why below).
 I have tested Android, and Java SE

Summary
This PR will:

Create a Log class in Android and JavaSE
Deprecate the log class in base/android/util
Replace usage of the Log class with DebugTool to standardize our logging (DebugTool and NativeLogTool will use the newly created Log classes)
With these changes we can safely remove the Log class from /base/android/util in the next major release

CLA

 I have signed the CLA

commit.message: Create Log Wrapper and Repace Base library logging
Wrap Log.java and move base logging to DebugTool

nodes.bodyText: Is there a reason for changing this from log.w to log.e?

commit.message: Start moving android logs to DebugTool
refactor android classes to use DebugTool
Use new logInfo API instead of Deprecated API
Move android and base classes to new logWarning
Move JavaSE classes to use new logWarning
Move logError to new DebugTool APIs in android/base
Move JavaSE classes to use the new logError Apis
